Element


property
&property.purpose;


&property.synopsis.gen;
Description



The notion of a Property is very domain-dependent in computer
documentation.  Some object-oriented systems speak of properties; the
components from which GUIs are constructed have properties;
and one can speak of properties in very general terms; the properties
of a relational database.




You might use Property for any of these in your documentation.


Processing expectations


&format.inline; &pexp.moreinfo;



&FutureChanges;


The content model of Property will be constrained to
(#PCDATA | Replaceable | InlineGraphic) in DocBook V4.0.




&property.parents.gen;
&property.children.gen;

Attributes

moreinfo



If MoreInfo is set to RefEntry,
it implies that a RefEntry exists which further describes the
Property.





